        "body": "Fixes #8246\r\n\r\n## Description\r\nWhen the Android system destroys and recreates the Activity while a file picker is open (due to backgrounding or memory pressure), the `ValueCallback` reference is lost, causing file uploads to fail silently.\r\n\r\nThis fix stores the file chooser callbacks in static variables so they survive activity recreation. When the activity result is received:\r\n- If the instance callback exists, it's used normally\r\n- If the instance callback is null, the static pending callback is used\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n- Added static variables to store pending file path callback, image URI, and file chooser type\r\n- Added `FileChooserType` enum to track which picker was opened\r\n- Added [handlePendingFileChooserResult()](cci:1://file:///Users/suryanshgupta/Desktop/a/capacitor/android/capacitor/src/main/java/com/getcapacitor/BridgeWebChromeClient.java:91:4-136:5) to handle results when activity was recreated\r\n- Added [clearPendingFileChooserState()](cci:1://file:///Users/suryanshgupta/Desktop/a/capacitor/android/capacitor/src/main/java/com/getcapacitor/BridgeWebChromeClient.java:138:4-145:5) to clean up static state\r\n- Updated [showImageCapturePicker()](cci:1://file:///Users/suryanshgupta/Desktop/a/capacitor/android/capacitor/src/main/java/com/getcapacitor/BridgeWebChromeClient.java:398:4-430:5), [showVideoCapturePicker()](cci:1://file:///Users/suryanshgupta/Desktop/a/capacitor/android/capacitor/src/main/java/com/getcapacitor/BridgeWebChromeClient.java:432:4-455:5), and [showFilePicker()](cci:1://file:///Users/suryanshgupta/Desktop/a/capacitor/android/capacitor/src/main/java/com/getcapacitor/BridgeWebChromeClient.java:457:4-496:5) to store callbacks before launching",
